      "content": "that's a pretty bleak take lol. isn't there also an argument that it's less about the UN being a \"failure\" and more just about the reality of how hard it is to get countries to actually agree on anything? like, is it even a fair critique to call it ineffective if they only have as much power as the member states actually give them?",
